                <div>
                  <p>
                    CitySafe is a web-based disaster response architecture that provides real-time alerts, localized
                    notifications, and reliable information during critical emergencies. It serves as a unified nexus
                    empowering citizens to stay informed, transmit SOS distress signals, and supports municipal
                    officials and responders in orchestrating rapid relief operations efficiently.
                  </p>
                  <div>
                    <!-- Decorative blur -->
                    <div></div>
                    <p>
                      CitySafe was developed as a capstone research initiative entitled <strong>“CitySafe: Urban Disaster Response App”</strong>.
                      The primary objective is establishing a resilient, efficient, and compassionate digital
                      infrastructure that amplifies disaster readiness and recovery in modern urban environments.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                      — System Architecture Research Initiative
